# Property Management Guide

## API Integration

### Services Structure
- `propertyAPIService` - Main service for property-related API calls
- `usePropertyStore` - Zustand store for property state management
- Axios configuration for backend communication

### Environment Variables
- `VITE_API_BASE_URL` - Backend API base URL for property services

### API Endpoints
- `GET /properties` - Search and filter properties
- `GET /properties/{id}` - Get single property details
- `GET /properties/recommendations` - Get recommended properties

## Property Filtering

### Filter Components
- `SimplifiedFilter` - Basic property filtering for simple use cases
- `AdvancedPropertyFilter` - Comprehensive filtering with multiple criteria
- `PropertyFilters` - Main filter component with location integration

### Filter Parameters
- Location-based: `lat`, `lng`, `radius`, `city`, `locality`
- Property type: `property_type` (apartment, villa, plot, commercial, etc.)
- Price range: `price_min`, `price_max`
- Property size: `area_min`, `area_max`
- Rooms: `bedrooms_min`, `bedrooms_max`, `bathrooms_min`, `bathrooms_max`
- Additional: `amenities`, `features`, `parking_spaces`, `age_max`

### Best Practices
1. Use location-based filtering with Google Places integration
2. Implement progressive disclosure for filter options
3. Provide sensible defaults for filter ranges
4. Cache filter results to improve performance
5. Handle empty states gracefully
6. Implement loading states for better UX

## Property Data Structure

### Property Object
```javascript
{
  id: number,                    // Unique property identifier
  title: string,                 // Property title
  description: string,           // Detailed description
  price: number,                 // Property price
  property_type: string,         // Type of property
  location: {                    // Location information
    lat: number,
    lng: number,
    address: string,
    city: string,
    locality: string
  },
  features: {                    // Property features
    bedrooms: number,
    bathrooms: number,
    area_sqft: number,
    parking_spaces: number,
    floor_number: number
  },
  amenities: string[],           // List of amenities
  images: string[],              // Property image URLs
  listing_type: 'sale' | 'rent', // Sale or rental listing
  created_at: string,            // Creation timestamp
  updated_at: string             // Last update timestamp
}
```

## State Management

### Property Store Actions
- `searchProperties(filters)` - Search properties with filters
- `getPropertyById(id)` - Get single property details
- `setFilters(filters)` - Update current filters
- `clearFilters()` - Reset all filters
- `setLoading(state)` - Set loading state
- `setError(error)` - Set error state

### Filter State Structure
```javascript
{
  location: { lat, lng, name },    // Current location
  property_type: [],               // Selected property types
  price_min: null,                 // Minimum price
  price_max: null,                 // Maximum price
  area_min: null,                  // Minimum area
  area_max: null,                  // Maximum area
  bedrooms_min: null,              // Minimum bedrooms
  bathrooms_min: null,             // Minimum bathrooms
  amenities: [],                   // Selected amenities
  sort_by: 'relevance'             // Sort criteria
}
```

## Property Pages

### Available Pages
- `PropertyDetails` - Individual property details page
- `PostProperty` - Form for posting new properties
- Various property listing pages with filters

### Page Integration
1. Use consistent filtering across all property pages
2. Implement breadcrumb navigation
3. Add property comparison features
4. Include contact forms for property inquiries
5. Implement property sharing functionality

## Performance Optimization

### API Optimization
- Implement debounced search for text inputs
- Use pagination for large result sets
- Cache frequently accessed data
- Implement proper error boundaries

### Component Optimization
- Use React.memo for filter components
- Implement virtual scrolling for large lists
- Lazy load property images
- Minimize re-renders with proper state management